An order with the ''CM'' order type, or a credit memo order, is used to account for unauthorized returns from customers; this order includes a reference to the original invoice. You can use credit memo orders to adjust completed sales orders and account for unauthorized returns. {br}{TOC} ==Order Type Activation== To give users in the system the ability to create credit memo orders, you need to select the ''CM'' order type on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SO_20_10_00|Order Types] ([~/?ScreenId=SO201000|SO201000]) form, select the '''Active''' check box, and save your changes. ==Template Settings==[anchor|#_0e901dca-9376-4111-9621-368cbe26d4de] Each predefined order type has an associated ''template'': a collection of settings that controls the processing of documents of the type, including what related documents it generates, whether it requires shipment, and how the automation behavior determines the conditions for changing the statuses of orders of the type. The template settings of the order type are displayed on the '''Template Settings''' tab of the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SO_20_10_00|Order Types] ([~/?ScreenId=SO201000|SO201000]) form.{br}
The ''CM'' order type has the following template settings:[anchor|#ul_xbj_rwx_bdb] *'''Automation Behavior''': ''Credit Memo'' *:The system uses the predefined ''Credit Memo'' workflow for a credit memo order. For more information, see [HelpRoot_Dev_Customization\CG_GL_Items_WorkflowConcept|Creating Workflows]. *'''Default Operation''': ''Receipt'' *:This is the default inventory operation to be performed for a credit memo order. *'''AR Document Type''': ''Credit Memo'' *:This setting means that an Accounts Receivable credit memo is generated during the processing of a credit memo order. *'''Process Shipments''': Cleared *:This setting means that no shipment is created during the processing of a credit memo order.
The template settings of the ''CM'' order type cannot be changed. If you want to modify the order processing, you can create a custom type based on the ''CM'' order type, and modify its settings based on your needs. For more information, see [HelpRoot_OrderMgmt\SO__con_Custom_Order_Types|Custom Sales Order Types]. ==Posting Settings== In the posting settings of the order type, you specify the set of rules for defining which accounts and subaccounts should be used to post General Ledger transactions during the processing of an order of this type. You specify the posting settings on the '''General Settings''' tab ('''Posting Settings''' section) of the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SO_20_10_00|Order Types] ([~/?ScreenId=SO201000|SO201000]) form. For more information, see [HelpRoot_OrderMgmt\SO__con_PostingSettings|Posting Settings in Sales Order Types]. ==Quick Processing of Credit Memo Orders== To give users the ability to quickly process a credit memo order from the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SO_30_10_00|Sales Orders] ([~/?ScreenId=SO301000|SO301000]) form, you need to select the '''Allow Quick Process''' check box on the '''Template Settings''' tab of the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SO_20_10_00|Order Types] ([~/?ScreenId=SO201000|SO201000]) form. For more information, see [HelpRoot_OrderMgmt\SO__con_Quick_Process_Workflow|Quick Processing of Sales Orders]. ==Approval of Credit Memo Orders== Approvals can be configured for credit memo orders, if needed, because the '''Supports Approval''' check box is selected (and cannot be cleared) for the ''CM'' order type on the '''General Settings''' tab of the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SO_20_10_00|Order Types] ([~/?ScreenId=SO201000|SO201000]) form.{br}
If your organization&rsquo;s policies require that orders of the ''CM'' type should be approved before processing, you can set up approval of credit memo orders. After approval has been configured, when a credit memo order is saved on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SO_30_10_00|Sales Orders] ([~/?ScreenId=SO301000|SO301000]) form, it will be assigned to an approver, and its status will change to ''Pending Approval''. If it has been rejected, the order should be corrected, and after the approver has edited the order, it will be automatically reassigned for approval. If it has been approved, the order may be processed to completion. For more information, see [HelpRoot_OrderMgmt\SO__con_Approvals|Sales Order Approval]. ==Calculation of Freight Charges== By default, freight is not calculated on credit memo orders. This is indicated by the '''Calculate Freight''' check box, which is cleared by default for the ''CM'' order type on the '''General Settings''' tab of the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SO_20_10_00|Order Types] ([~/?ScreenId=SO201000|SO201000]) form. For more information on the configuration and calculation of freight, see [HelpRoot_OrderMgmt\CS__con_Freight_Calculation|Freight Calculation]. ==Configuration of Document Processing== In the ''CM'' order type settings, you can specify how the system processes the orders of this type and related documents that are generated during the processing of a ''CM'' order. For more information, see [HelpRoot_OrderMgmt\SO__con_AffectingProcessingDocs|Changing the Processing of Sales Documents].

To process a return of items that were sold in a cash sale and do not require shipping, you create a cash return order (that is, an order of the ''CR'' order type). {br}{TOC} ==Activation of the Order Type== To give users in the system the ability to create cash return orders, you need to select the ''CR'' order type on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SO_20_10_00|Order Types] ([~/?ScreenId=SO201000|SO201000]) form, select the '''Active''' check box, and save your changes. ==Template Settings==[anchor|#_5564b031-78cc-4220-b2c8-e39bbf95da5c] Each predefined order type has an associated ''template'': a collection of settings that controls the processing of documents of the type, including what related documents it generates, whether it requires shipment, and how the automation behavior determines the conditions for changing the statuses of orders of the type. The template settings of the order type are displayed on the '''Template Settings''' tab of the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SO_20_10_00|Order Types] ([~/?ScreenId=SO201000|SO201000]) form.{br}
The ''CR'' order type has the following template settings:[anchor|#ul_fn5_rwx_bdb] *'''Automation Behavior''': ''Invoice'' *:The system uses the predefined ''Invoice'' workflow for a cash return order. For more information, see [HelpRoot_Dev_Customization\CG_GL_Items_WorkflowConcept|Creating Workflows]. *'''Default Operation''': ''Receipt'' *:This is the default inventory operation to be performed for a cash return order. *'''AR Document Type''': ''Cash Return'' *:This setting means that an Accounts Receivable cash return is generated during the processing of a cash return order. *'''Process Shipments''': Cleared *:This setting means that no shipment is created during the processing of a cash return.
Although the template settings of the ''CR'' order type can be edited, we do not recommend that you modify them. If you want to modify the order processing, you can create a custom type based on the ''CR'' order type, and modify its settings based on your needs. For more information, see [HelpRoot_OrderMgmt\SO__con_Custom_Order_Types|Custom Sales Order Types].'''Posting Settings''' In the posting settings of the order type, you specify the set of rules for defining which accounts and subaccounts should be used to post General Ledger transactions during the processing of an order of this order type. You specify the posting settings on the '''General Settings''' tab ('''Posting Settings''' section) of the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SO_20_10_00|Order Types] ([~/?ScreenId=SO201000|SO201000]) form. For more information, see [HelpRoot_OrderMgmt\SO__con_PostingSettings|Posting Settings in Sales Order Types]. ==Quick Processing of Cash Return Orders== To give users the ability to quickly process a cash return order from the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SO_30_10_00|Sales Orders] ([~/?ScreenId=SO301000|SO301000]) form, you need to select the '''Allow Quick Process''' check box on the '''Template Settings''' tab of the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SO_20_10_00|Order Types] ([~/?ScreenId=SO201000|SO201000]) form. For more information, see [HelpRoot_OrderMgmt\SO__con_Quick_Process_Workflow|Quick Processing of Sales Orders]. ==Approval of Cash Return Orders== Approvals can be configured for cash return orders, if needed, because the '''Supports Approval''' check box is selected (and cannot be cleared) for the ''CR'' order type on the '''General Settings''' tab of the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SO_20_10_00|Order Types] ([~/?ScreenId=SO201000|SO201000]) form.{br}
If your organization&rsquo;s policies require that orders of the ''CR'' type should be approved before processing, you can set up approval of cash return orders. After approval has been configured, when an order is saved on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SO_30_10_00|Sales Orders] ([~/?ScreenId=SO301000|SO301000]) form, it will be assigned to an approver, and its status will change to ''Pending Approval''. If it has been rejected, the order should be corrected, and after the approver has edited the order, it will be automatically reassigned for approval. If it has been approved, the order may be processed further. For more information, see [HelpRoot_OrderMgmt\SO__con_Approvals|Sales Order Approval]. ==Calculation of Freight Charges== By default, freight is calculated on cash return orders. This is indicated by the '''Calculate Freight''' check box, which is selected by default for the ''CR'' type on the '''General Settings''' tab of the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SO_20_10_00|Order Types] ([~/?ScreenId=SO201000|SO201000]) form. For more information on configuring and calculating freight, see [HelpRoot_OrderMgmt\CS__con_Freight_Calculation|Freight Calculation]. ==Configuration of Document Processing== In the ''CR'' order type settings, you can specify how the system processes orders of this type and related documents that are generated during the processing of a ''CR'' order. For more information, see [HelpRoot_OrderMgmt\SO__con_AffectingProcessingDocs|Changing the Processing of Sales Documents]. ==Related Articles== *[HelpRoot_OrderMgmt\SO__con_scn_Return_for_Cash|Processing Return for Cash]

