Also, on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SO_20_10_00|Order Types] ([~/?ScreenId=SO201000|SO201000]) form, the ''SO'' order type has been configured and activated.{br}
On the [HelpRoot_FormReference\IN_20_25_00|Stock Items] ([~/?ScreenId=IN202500|IN202500]) form, the ''ORANGES'' stock item has been defined.{br}
On the [HelpRoot_FormReference\AR_30_30_00|Customers] ([~/?ScreenId=AR303000|AR303000]) form, the ''GOODFOOD (GoodFood One Restaurant)'' customer has been defined. Additionally, the sales documents that you need to correct have been processed in the system: A sales order for ''GOODFOOD '' has been created, a shipment for the sales order has been prepared and confirmed, and an SO invoice has been prepared, released, and paid in full. ==Process Overview== To be able to correct the SO invoice that was processed and paid, you will first reverse the payment on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\AR_30_20_00|Payments and Applications] ([~/?ScreenId=AR302000|AR302000]) form. Then on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SO_30_30_00|Invoices] ([~/?ScreenId=SO303000|SO303000]) form, you will create a correction invoice with the correct unit price and release this invoice, which will cause the system to cancel the invoice with the incorrect data and apply a credit memo to it. You will then apply the payment to the correction invoice. ==System Preparation== Do the following:[anchor|#_73ebb003-1b19-4747-9eea-982486c72ff9][anchor|#_87261bd8-0ea9-4df0-a769-dbc270af0e37] #Launch the Acumatica ERP website, and sign in to a company with the ''U100'' dataset preloaded. To sign in as a sales and purchasing manager, use the ''wiley'' login and the ''123'' password. #In the info area, in the upper-right corner of the top pane of the Acumatica ERP screen, make sure that the business date in your system is set to ''1/30/2019''. If a different date is displayed, click the Business Date menu button, and select ''1/30/2019'' on the calendar. For simplicity, in this activity, you will create and process all documents in the system on this business date.
==Step 1: Reversing the Payment== To reverse the payment that has been applied to the SO invoice that you are going to correct, do the following:[anchor|#_fa742785-635f-4638-890f-918dff014a89] #On the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SO_30_10_00|Sales Orders] ([~/?ScreenId=SO301000|SO301000]) form, open the sales order for the ''GOODFOOD'' customer in the amount of $210.66, dated ''1/21/2019''. #In the '''Invoice Nbr.''' column on the '''Shipments''' tab, click the link to open the SO invoice prepared for the sales order on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SO_30_30_00|Invoices] ([~/?ScreenId=SO303000|SO303000]) form. #:In the Summary area of the form, notice that the SO invoice is assigned the ''Closed'' status because it was paid in full. You need to reverse the payment to be able to correct the invoice. #On the '''Applications''' tab, click the link in the '''Reference Nbr.''' column of the only row to open the payment that was applied to invoice on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\AR_30_20_00|Payments and Applications] ([~/?ScreenId=AR302000|AR302000]) form. #On the table toolbar of the '''Application History''' tab, click '''Reverse Application'''. #On the form toolbar, click '''Release''' to release the reversal of the payment application. #:On the '''Application History''' tab, a reversing line for the full payment amount appears. The payment application is now reversed; the payment is assigned the ''Open'' status.
==Step 2: Creating the Correction Invoice== Now that you have reversed the payment, you can create the correction SO invoice as follows:[anchor|#_157bbfb8-a804-4c3c-b8df-06b8f140a5bc] #While you are still viewing the payment you have reversed on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\AR_30_20_00|Payments and Applications] ([~/?ScreenId=AR302000|AR302000]) form, on the '''Application History''' tab, click the link in the '''Reference Nbr.''' column of either row to open the SO invoice on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SO_30_30_00|Invoices] ([~/?ScreenId=SO303000|SO303000]) form. Notice that invoice is now assigned the ''Open'' status. #On the form toolbar, click '''Actions''' > '''Correct Invoice'''. The system creates a correction invoice and opens it on the same form. #On the form toolbar, click '''Save''' to save the prepared invoice. The system displays a warning on the '''Financial Details''' tab indicating that the current document is the correction document. #In the only line on the '''Document Details''' tab, change the '''Unit Price''' to ''1.99''. #On the form toolbar, click'''Release from Hold''' and then click '''Release'''. Notice that the invoice is assigned the ''Open'' status. #On the '''Financial Details''' tab, click the '''Original Document''' link to open the original invoice (that is, the invoice that was corrected) on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SO_30_30_00|Invoices] form. #On the '''Applications''' tab, review the line with the ''Credit Memo'' document type, as shown in the following screenshot. The credit memo was automatically generated when you released the correction invoice and was applied to the original document; this is why the original invoice is now assigned the ''Canceled'' status, as you can also see in the screenshot.[anchor|#_99f97f2d-5e3e-4fee-a2bd-2fa68f0733b3][image:UserGuide/Images/activity_OrderMgmt_SO_Invoice_Correction.png|popup|The original invoice, which is now canceled|450px] #On the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SO_30_10_00|Sales Orders] (