==Step 3: Applying a Payment to Correction Document== To apply the payment to the correction SO invoice that you have created, do the following:[anchor|#_6da246db-768d-4667-b69f-ddd91da4395d] #On the [HelpRoot_FormReference\AR_30_20_00|Payments and Applications] ([~/?ScreenId=AR302000|AR302000]) form, open the payment to ''GOODFOOD'' in the amount of $210.66. #On the '''Documents to Apply''' tab, add a new line with the ''Invoice'' type, and in the '''Reference Nbr.''' box, select the reference number of the correction invoice that you have created earlier in this activity. #On the form toolbar, click '''Release'''. Due to the changed price of the oranges, the payment still has an available balance of $11.33 that can be applied to any other customer invoice (which is shown in the '''Available Balance''' box in the Summary area). #On the '''Application History''' tab, click the reference number of the invoice to which you applied the payment (that is, the correction invoice), to open it on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SO_30_30_00|Invoices] ([~/?ScreenId=SO303000|SO303000]) form. The invoice that was paid is now assigned the ''Closed'' status.
You have finished the process of correcting the SO invoice.

The following activity will walk you through the process of canceling an SO invoice that was created for a sales order.[anchor|#_0bada5bb-d40a-46e1-ba9c-ce44a5487515]((({S:Danger}The following activity is based on the ''U100'' dataset. If you are using another dataset, or if any system settings have been changed in ''U100'', these changes can affect the workflow of the activity and the results of the processing. To avoid any issues, restore the ''U100'' dataset to its initial state. ))) ==Story== Suppose that on January 28, 2020, FourStar Coffee & Sweets Shop ordered 15 pounds of apples from the main office of SweetLife. The ordered fruits were shipped from the Wholesale warehouse to the customer&rsquo;s location, and the SO invoice was prepared. Further suppose that you later noticed that the sales taxes had not been calculated for the SO invoice because the ''EXEMPT'' tax category had been specified in the sales order line by mistake. Acting as a sales manager, you need to cancel the incorrect invoice and create a new one with the correct information. ==Configuration Overview== For the purposes of this lesson, the ''Inventory'' feature, which provides the ability to create sales and purchase orders that include stock items, have been enabled on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\CS_10_00_00|Enable/Disable Features] ([~/?ScreenId=CS100000|CS100000]) form.{br}
Also, on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SO_20_10_00|Order Types] ([~/?ScreenId=SO201000|SO201000]) form, the ''SO'' order type has been configured and activated.{br}
On the [HelpRoot_FormReference\IN_20_25_00|Stock Items] ([~/?ScreenId=IN202500|IN202500]) form, the ''APPLES'' stock item has been defined.{br}
On the [HelpRoot_FormReference\AR_30_30_00|Customers] ([~/?ScreenId=AR303000|AR303000]) form, the ''COFFEESHOP (FourStar Coffee & Sweets Shop)'' customer has been defined. Additionally, the sales documents that you need to correct have been processed in the system: a sales order to ''COFFEESHOP'' has been created, a shipment for the sales order has been prepared and confirmed, and an SO invoice has been prepared and released. ==Process Overview== To correct the mistake of taxes not being charged on the SO invoice on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SO_30_30_00|Invoices] ([~/?ScreenId=SO303000|SO303000]) form, you will cancel the invoice. Then you will change the tax category in the sales order line on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SO_30_10_00|Sales Orders] ([~/?ScreenId=SO301000|SO301000]) form, and prepare a new SO invoice for the sales order with the correct information. ==System Preparation== Do the following:[anchor|#_73ebb003-1b19-4747-9eea-982486c72ff9][anchor|#_a239db67-84ae-4707-a766-9d698eadf94b] #Launch the Acumatica ERP website, and sign in to a company with the ''U100'' dataset preloaded. To sign in as a sales and purchasing manager, use the ''wiley'' login and the ''123'' password. #In the info area, in the upper-right corner of the top pane of the Acumatica ERP screen, make sure that the business date in your system is set to 1/30/2020. If a different date is displayed, click the Business Date menu button, and select 1/30/2020 on the calendar. For simplicity, in this activity, you will create and process all documents in the system on this business date.
==Step 1: Canceling the SO Invoice== To cancel the SO invoice with the incorrect tax category, do the following:[anchor|#_fa742785-635f-4638-890f-918dff014a89] #On the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SO_30_10_00|Sales Orders] ([~/?ScreenId=SO301000|SO301000]) form, open the sales order for the ''COFFEESHOP'' customer in the amount of $37.50, dated ''1/28/2020''. #On the '''Shipments''' tab, click the '''Invoice Nbr.''' link to open the SO invoice on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SO_30_30_00|Invoices] ([~/?ScreenId=SO303000|SO303000]) form. #Review the '''Tax Details''' tab. Notice that the ''NYNOTAX'' tax code with the 0% tax rate has been applied to the SO invoice, so the tax amount is $0.00, which is incorrect. #On the form toolbar, click '''Actions''' > '''Cancel Invoice'''. #The system creates a cancellation credit memo with the same settings as the invoice you were viewing, and opens it on the same form. #On the form toolbar, click '''Release from Hold''' and then click '''Release'''. The credit memo is assigned the ''Closed'' status, because it has been applied in full to the invoice. #On the '''Financial Details''' tab, click the link in the '''Original Document''' box to open the invoice that was canceled on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SO_30_30_00|Invoices] form. Notice that the invoice is now assigned the ''Canceled'' status.
