301000|SO301000]) form, or you can create any number of invoices by running the ''Prepare Invoice'' action for multiple selected orders on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SO_50_10_00|Process Orders] ([~/?ScreenId=SO501000|SO501000]) form. {br}
The prepared document or documents of the ''Credit Memo'' type can be reviewed on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SO_30_30_00|Invoices] ([~/?ScreenId=SO303000|SO303000]) form. You can print an SO invoice by clicking '''Reports &gt; Print Invoice''' on the form toolbar of this form. ==4. Release the Sales Orders Invoice== For the credit memo order, the released Sales Orders invoice acts as a shipment does: On release of the invoice, the system updates the '''Qty. on Shipments''' value in the order lines based on the quantity specified in the credit memo lines, and inserts the reference number of the Sales Orders credit memo on the '''Shipments''' tab of the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SO_30_10_00|Sales Orders] ([~/?ScreenId=SO301000|SO301000]) form.{br}
When the SO invoice is released, a batch of General Ledger transactions is generated, and the system automatically generates an inventory issue with the ''Credit Memo'' transaction type that adds the returned item to inventory. Also, a corresponding Accounts Receivable credit memo is generated and becomes available for review on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\AR_30_10_00|Invoices and Memos] ([~/?ScreenId=AR301000|AR301000]) form. ==5. Release the Inventory Issue== The generated inventory issue is released automatically if the '''Automatically Release IN Documents''' check box is selected on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SO_10_10_00|Sales Orders Preferences] ([~/?ScreenId=SO101000|SO101000]) form. If this check box is cleared, you have to release the inventory issue manually by clicking '''Release''' on the form toolbar of the [HelpRoot_FormReference\IN_30_20_00|Issues] ([~/?ScreenId=IN302000|IN302000]) form. On release of the inventory issue, a batch of General Ledger Transactions is generated.((({S:Warn}To finish the return process, you need to process Accounts Receivable credit memo to completion. You can apply the credit memo to the original invoice, or process the customer refund if the original invoice was already paid. For details on credit memo application, see [HelpRoot_Financials\Finance_CorrectingARInvoices_Process_Activity|AR Invoice Correction: To Create a Credit Memo]. For details on the processing of a customer refund, see[HelpRoot_Financials\Finance_ProcessingCustomerRefunds_Activity1|Customer Refunds: To Create a Customer Refund]. ))) ==Related Articles== *[HelpRoot_OrderMgmt\SO__CNF_OrderType_CM|CM Order Type (Credit Memo)] *[HelpRoot_OrderMgmt\SO__How_Process_CM|To Process a Credit Memo Order (CM)] *[HelpRoot_Financials\Finance_ProcessingCustomerRefunds_Activity1|Customer Refunds: To Create a Customer Refund]

