The prepared document or documents of the ''Cash Return'' type can be reviewed on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SO_30_30_00|Invoices] ([~/?ScreenId=SO303000|SO303000]) form. You can print an SO invoice by clicking '''Reports &gt; Print Invoice''' on the form toolbar of the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SO_30_30_00|Invoices] ([~/?ScreenId=SO303000|SO303000]) form. ==4. Release the Sales Orders Invoice== When the Sales Orders invoice of the ''Cash Return'' type is released, the system automatically generates an inventory issue with the ''Credit Memo'' transaction type that adds the returned item to inventory; you can review the generated issue on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\IN_30_20_00|Issues] ([~/?ScreenId=IN302000|IN302000]) form. Also, the related Accounts Receivable cash return with the same reference number becomes available for reviewing on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\AR_30_40_00|Cash Sales] ([~/?ScreenId=AR304000|AR304000]) form. The document updates the appropriate sales and cash accounts. ==5. Release the Inventory Issue== The generated inventory issue is released automatically if the '''Automatically Release IN Documents''' check box is selected on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SO_10_10_00|Sales Orders Preferences] form. If this check box is cleared, you have to release the inventory issue manually by clicking '''Release''' on the form toolbar of the [HelpRoot_FormReference\IN_30_20_00|Issues] ([~/?ScreenId=IN302000|IN302000]) form. On release of the inventory issue, a batch of General Ledger Transactions is generated.

Acumatica ERP gives you the flexibility to manage various types of customer returns. Depending on your company&rsquo;s return policies, you may need to perform a merchandise authorization return of an inventory item for possible credit and replacement. For this purpose, you an use a merchandise authorization return order, and you can send the customer a printed or electronic copy of it along with the goods to be returned. Once the goods are received by your organization, they are returned to inventory, and the customer receives other goods instead. For this type of return order, different items than those returned may be included for replacement, freight and shipping and handling charges may be included, and the items could be returned at higher or lower prices. {br}
To process a merchandise authorization return, you can use a return order of the ''RM'' predefined order type. The processing of a ''RM'' order (further in this topic referred to as a ''return order'') involves the actions and generated documents shown in the following diagram.[anchor|#_3326672c-df88-4115-9a58-004ddcbb5bbf][anchor|#_0b20fe5c-67fd-4336-8568-a858d1353048][image:UserGuide/Images/diag_OrderMgmt_Return_at_Another_Price.png|popup|450px] The following sections describe in detail the processing steps shown in the diagram.{br}{TOC} ==1. Enter the Merchandise Return Order== You create a new return order of the ''RM'' order type on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SO_30_10_00|Sales Orders] ([~/?ScreenId=SO301000|SO301000]) form. A reference number for the new return order is generated according to the numbering sequence assigned to this order type on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SO_20_10_00|Order Types] ([~/?ScreenId=SO201000|SO201000]) form. If the order is created with the ''On Hold'' status, you should click '''Release from Hold''' on the form toolbar to process the order further.. ==2. Link the Original Invoice Line to the Order== Each return line in an order of the ''RM'' order type could include a reference to the original invoice for which the return is performed. To add an item to be returned and include a link to the original invoice, on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SO_30_10_00|Sales Orders] ([~/?ScreenId=SO301000|SO301000]) form, you can click '''Add Invoice''' on the table toolbar of the '''Document Details''' tab and select the line of the needed invoice in the '''Add Invoice Details''' dialog box (which opens). ((({S:Warn}You can also add a stock item to be returned without linking it to an invoice. To do this, click '''Add Stock Item''' on the table toolbar of the '''Document Details''' tab, and select the item in the '''Inventory Lookup''' dialog box (which opens). ))) An added return line (whether or not it is linked to an invoice) has the ''Receipt'' operation specified in the '''Operation''' column. After you have added the ''Receipt'' lines, make sure that the '''Auto-Create Issue''' check box is cleared in these lines (because you need to add replacement items and specify their details manually). ==3. Add a Line with the Item for Replacement== Each line with the ''Receipt'' transaction type in an ''RM'' order should have a corresponding line with the ''Issue'' operation type for a replacement item. You need to add an ''Issue''-type line for the replacement lines manually. Alternatively, if the returned item is not tracked by serial or lot numbers, and the item price wasn&rsquo;t changed between the original sale and return, you can select the '''Auto-Create Issue''' check box for the line; on shipment confirmation, the system will add the corresponding ''Issue''-type lines automatically and copy the line details from the ''Receipt''-type lines. ==4a–4b. Process the Return and the Replacement== To complete the order, you need to process the receipt of the returned item and the shipment of the replacement item. You can process the return and replacement in any order on its own, or you can process multiple returns and replacements simultaneously on mass-processing forms. You perform the following general steps for processing: [anchor|#_228a8628-2ef3-4115-aaae-ce8fbd6b3cec] #Prepare the receipt (for return) and the shipment (for replacement) by doing the following: #*You prepare the receipt (that is, the incoming shipment with the ''Receipt'' operation type) by clicking '''Actions''' > '''Create Receipt''' on the form toolbar of the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SO_30_10_00|Sales Orders] ([~/?ScreenId=SO301000|SO301000]) form. #*You prepare the outgoing shipment with the ''Issue'' operation type by clicking '''Actions''' > '''Create Shipment''' on the form toolbar of the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SO_30_10_00|Sales Orders] form. #:The prepared shipment can be reviewed on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SO_30_20_00|Shipments] ([~/?ScreenId=SO302000|SO302000]) form. #:Alternatively, you can use the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SO_50_10_00|Process Orders] ([~/?ScreenId=SO501000|SO501000]) form to create both incoming and outgoing shipments for one order or multiple orders. To do this, you select the ''Create Shipment'' action, select the needed orders, and click '''Process''' on the form toolbar. #Confirm the receipt and the shipment. #:You can confirm a particular receipt or shipment by clicking '''Actions''' > '''Confirm Shipment''' on the form toolbar of the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SO_30_20_00|Shipments] form; to confirm multiple shipments, you can select the ''Confirm Shipment'' action, select the needed shipments, and click '''Process''' on the form toolbar of the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SO_50_30_00|Process Shipments] ([~/?ScreenId=SO503000|SO503000]) form. #Prepare the SO invoices. #:You prepare the Sales Orders invoice for a particular receipt or shipment by clicking '''Actions''' > '''Prepare Invoice''' on the form toolbar on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SO_30_20_00|Shipments] form, or you can create invoices by processing the ''Prepare Invoice'' action for multiple selected shipments on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SO_50_30_00|Process Shipments] form. #:The prepared document or documents can be reviewed on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SO_30_30_00|Invoices] ([~/?ScreenId=SO303000|SO303000]) form. For the return, the system generates an SO invoice of the ''Credit Memo'' type; for the shipment, the system generates an SO invoice of the ''Invoice'' type. #:You can print an SO invoice by clicking '''Reports &gt; Print Invoice''' on the form toolbar of the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SO_30_30_00|Invoices] form. #Release the SO invoices. #:When the SO invoices are released, the system automatically generates two inventory issues: one with the ''Return'' transaction type for the return, and one with the ''Issue'' transaction type for replacement. Also, the related Accounts Receivable credit memo and invoice with the same reference numbers become available for reviewing on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\AR_30_10_00|Invoices and Memos] ([~/?ScreenId=AR301000|AR301000]) form. #:Once you release the SO invoices, the original ''RM'' order is assigned the ''Completed'' status. #Release the generated inventory issues. #:The generated inventory issues are released automatically if the '''Automatically Release IN Documents''' check box is selected on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SO_10_10_00|Sales Orders Preferences] ([~/?ScreenId=SO101000|SO101000]) form. If this check box is cleared, you have to release each inventory issue manually by clicking '''Release''' on the form toolbar of the [HelpRoot_FormReference\IN_30_20_00|Issues] ([~/?ScreenId=IN302000|IN302000]) form. On release of each inventory issue, a batch of the General Ledger transactions is generated.
