==Printing Invoices==
To prepare a printable form of the invoice that is being processed, you use the [HelpRoot_ReportReference\SO_64_30_00|Invoice / Memo] ([~/?ScreenId=SO643000|SO643000]) report. While you are viewing an SO invoice on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SO_30_30_00|Invoices] ([~/?ScreenId=SO303000|SO303000]) form, you can navigate to this report by clicking '''Reports &gt; Print Invoice''' on the form toolbar. The system opens the printable version of the invoice on the [HelpRoot_ReportReference\SO_64_30_00|Invoice / Memo] report; then you can review the invoice and print it by clicking '''Print''' on the report toolbar.

In Acumatica ERP, you can create sales orders whose goods are intended for drop shipping. Drop shipping means that a customer orders the goods from your company, pays your company for the order, and receives the goods (which your company has ordered) directly from one of your vendors. With the ''Drop Shipments'' feature enabled on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\CS_10_00_00|Enable/Disable Features] ([~/?ScreenId=CS100000|CS100000]) form, you can mark particular goods for drop-shipping and create drop-ship orders for these goods. {br}{TOC} ==Learning Objectives== In this chapter, you will learn how to do the following:[anchor|#ul_pqx_cyf_hy] *Configure the processing of drop shipments in Acumatica ERP *Mark items for drop shipment in a sales order *Create a drop-ship purchase order for a sales order and process the drop shipment to completion *Mass-process drop shipments *Process the sales order and related purchase documents, inventory documents, and accounts payable documents *Find the information about documents related to drop shipment
==Applicable Scenarios== You use drop shipment to fulfill a sales order with items that your company does not have in stock. The standard process for fulfilling such a sales order is to create a sales order and mark the items for drop shipping, and then create a purchase order to purchase these items from the vendor, which ships the items directly to the customer. You then process a purchase receipt and an SO invoice when the customer has received the items. ==Drop-Shipment Process== To process a sale with drop shipment, you create a sales order of the ''SO'' order type on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SO_30_10_00|Sales Orders] ([~/?ScreenId=SO301000|SO301000]) form, and add the stock items ordered by the customer. You mark items for drop shipping by selecting the check box in the '''Mark for PO''' column and selecting ''Drop-Ship'' in the '''PO Source''' column, which means that the items will be ordered from the vendor and shipped directly to the customer. The system does not allocate stock items in inventory based on the quantities of goods and the document amounts on sales orders for drop shipping. {br}
When you mark items for drop shipping, the system creates purchase requests of the ''Drop-Ship'' plan type. You create drop-ship purchase orders by processing ''Drop-Ship'' purchase requests on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\PO_50_50_00|Create Purchase Orders] ([~/?ScreenId=PO505000|PO505000]) form. Each drop-ship purchase order generated from purchase requests contains links to the related sales order. The items from this purchase order are not shipped to the company's warehouse; rather, they are shipped directly to the customer. After you have received confirmation that the customer has received the goods from the vendor, you prepare and release the purchase receipt for the drop-ship purchase order. When you release the purchase receipt (which functions as a shipment document for drop-ship lines of sales orders), the status of the drop-ship purchase order is changed to ''Closed''; the sales order is assigned the ''Completed'' status, and then you prepare an SO invoice to the customer.{br}
On release of a purchase receipt prepared for drop-ship purchase order, the system does not create an inventory receipt, because the items are not received to inventory and are instead delivered directly to the customer. The quantities of stock items on completed drop-ship orders are not included in the quantities available at any warehouse of your company. ==Workflow of a Sale with Drop-Shipment== For a sales order that includes stock items intended for drop shipping, the typical processing involves the actions and generated documents shown in the following diagram.[anchor|#fig_ygr_p4d_h5][anchor|#image_dc1_xyx_2t][image:UserGuide/Images/diag_Sale_for_Dropship.png|popup|350px] ==Known Limitations== Return of drop-shipped stock items is supported only if these stock items have been received from a customer to the company&rsquo;s warehouse. In the purchase return document, the lines with drop-shipped stock items must be issued from the company&rsquo;s warehouse. Before you process a return, make sure that the drop-shipment processing has been completed (that is, the purchase receipt prepared for a drop-ship purchase order has been billed, and the invoice has been prepared and released for the related sales order).

You can create multiple drop-ship purchase orders for sales orders at the same time by mass-processing purchase requests of the ''Drop-Ship'' type on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\PO_50_50_00|Create Purchase Orders] ([~/?ScreenId=PO505000|PO505000]) form. ==To Create Drop-Ship Purchase Orders For Multiple Sales Orders==[anchor|#_cb5a50d3-bfa8-41de-9f24-5625d0203004] #Open the [HelpRoot_FormReference\PO_50_50_00|Create Purchase Orders] ([~/?ScreenId=PO505000|PO505000]) form. #Optional: In the '''Order Type''' box of the Selection area of the form, select ''SO'' or a custom order type used in your organization for drop shipping. #If needed, change the '''Creation Date''', which is the date on which the purchase order will be generated. #In the table, select the unlabeled check boxes in the rows of the needed lines with the ''Drop-Ship'' type, and make sure each of the selected lines has the proper vendor specified. #Click '''Process''' on the form toolbar, or click '''Process All''' to generate purchase orders for all listed sales orders. The system generates the drop-ship purchase orders.
==Notes About the Procedure==[anchor|#_874a2b8d-cba5-4d4b-8fbc-2a0237d902ef] The notes in this section describe the nuances of the UI elements available on the form, such as when an element is required and when it is not, and when the system fills in settings by default. This section can include other notes.{br}
