In Acumatica ERP, you can create sales orders whose goods are intended for drop shipping. Drop shipping means that a customer orders the goods from your company, pays your company for the order, and receives the goods (which your company has ordered) directly from one of your vendors. In the system, you define these goods as non-stock items because your company does not keep them in stock.{br}
If the ''Drop Shipments'' feature is enabled on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\CS_10_00_00|Enable/Disable Features] ([~/?ScreenId=CS100000|CS100000]) form, you can mark particular non-stock items for drop shipping and create drop-ship orders for these items. [anchor|#section_j1t_try_klb] ==Learning Objectives== In this chapter, you will learn how to do the following:[anchor|#ul_pqx_cyf_hy] *Process a sales order for non-stock items to be drop-shipped *Mark items for drop shipment in a sales order *Create a drop-ship purchase order for the sales order and process the drop shipment to completion [anchor|#section_k1t_try_klb] ==Applicable Scenarios== You use a drop shipment to fulfill a sale of non-stock items that your company does not keep in its warehouses. Instead, your company processes the needed documents to have your vendor ship the items directly to the customer[anchor|#section_l1t_try_klb] ==Drop-Shipping Process== To process a sale with drop shipment, you create a sales order of the ''SO'' order type on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SO_30_10_00|Sales Orders] ([~/?ScreenId=SO301000|SO301000]) form, and add the non-stock items ordered by the customer. On the '''Document Details''' tab of the form, you mark the non-stock items for drop shipping by selecting the check box in the '''Mark for PO''' column and selecting ''Drop-Ship'' in the '''PO Source''' column, which means that the items will be ordered from the vendor and shipped directly to the customer.{br}
When you mark items for drop shipping and save the sales order with the ''Open'' status, the system creates purchase requests of the ''Drop-Ship'' plan type. You then create a drop-ship purchase order by processing ''Drop-Ship'' purchase requests on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\PO_50_50_00|Create Purchase Orders] ([~/?ScreenId=PO505000|PO505000]) form. This drop-ship purchase order contains links to the related sales order.{br}
The items from this purchase order are not shipped to the company&rsquo;s warehouse; rather, they are shipped directly to the customer. After you have received confirmation that the customer has received the items from the vendor, you prepare and release the purchase receipt for the drop-ship purchase order. When you release the purchase receipt (which is listed as a shipment document for the sales order on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SO_30_10_00|Sales Orders] ([~/?ScreenId=SO301000|SO301000]) form), the status of the drop-ship purchase order and sales order is changed to ''Completed''. You can then you prepare an SO invoice for the customer.[anchor|#section_m1t_try_klb] ==Workflow of a Sale with Drop Shipment== For a sales order with non-stock items intended for drop shipment, the typical processing involves the actions and generated documents shown in the following diagram.[anchor|#fig_ygr_p4d_h5][anchor|#image_dc1_xyx_2t][image:UserGuide/Images/diag_Sale_Non-Stock_for_Dropship.png|popup|350px]

[anchor|#section_nlw_wry_klb] The following activity will walk you through the process of preparing a sales order with non-stock items marked for drop shipping and processing this sales order to completion.[anchor|#_9b82fce2-7dc1-4fab-95f1-c2c8a941533f]((({S:Danger}The following activity is based on the ''U100'' dataset. If you are using another dataset, or if any system settings have been changed in ''U100'', these changes can affect the workflow of the activity and the results of the processing. To avoid any issues, restore the ''U100'' dataset to its initial state. )))[anchor|#section_olw_wry_klb] ==Story== Suppose that the FourStar Coffee & Sweets Shop (''COFFEESHOP'') customer has ordered two rare teas at SweetLife’s retail store. Although these teas are presented in SweetLife’s website catalog, the company does not keep them in the wholesale or retail warehouse; they are defined in Acumatica ERP as non-stock items. When a customer orders these teas, SweetLife drop-ships them from the Tea & Spices (''TEACOMPANY'') vendor, which regularly stocks these teas, directly to the customer who ordered the teas. To fulfill the customer’s request, acting as the sales manager of the SweetLife store, you need to process a drop shipment. [anchor|#section_plw_wry_klb] ==Configuration Overview== For the purposes of this activity, the ''Drop Shipments'' feature, which provides the ability to create and process sales orders with drop shipment, has been enabled on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\CS_10_00_00|Enable/Disable Features] ([~/?ScreenId=CS100000|CS100000]) form.{br}
The following entities, which you will use in this activity, have been predefined in the system:[anchor|#ul_itw_4h4_blb] *On the [HelpRoot_FormReference\AP_30_30_00|Vendors] ([~/?ScreenId=AP303000|AP303000]) form, the ''TEACOMPANY'' vendor has been configured. *On the [HelpRoot_FormReference\IN_20_20_00|Non-Stock Items] ([~/?ScreenId=IN202000|IN202000]) form, the ''EMPTEA'' and ''KINGTEA'' non-stock items have been configured. For each of these items, the ''TEACOMPANY'' vendor has been added to the '''Vendor Details''' tab. Also, the '''Require Receipt''' and '''Require Shipment''' check boxes have been selected for these items on the '''General Settings''' tab. These settings are required to process drop-ship sales. [anchor|#section_qlw_wry_klb] ==Process Overview== In this activity, to process a sale with drop shipment, you will create a sales order of the ''SO'' order type on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SO_30_10_00|Sales Orders] ([~/?ScreenId=SO301000|SO301000]) form; on the '''Document Details''' tab, you will add the items ordered by the customer. Because the items are not kept in stock, you will mark each of them for drop shipping by selecting the check box in the '''Mark for PO''' column and selecting ''Drop-Ship'' in the '''PO Source''' column, which means that the items will be ordered from the vendor and shipped directly to the customer.{br}
You will then create a drop-ship purchase order by processing purchase requests of the ''Drop-Ship'' plan type on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\PO_50_50_00|Create Purchase Orders] ([~/?ScreenId=PO505000|PO505000]) form. The drop-ship purchase order generated from purchase requests, which can be viewed and processed further on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\PO_30_10_00|Purchase Orders] ([~/?ScreenId=PO301000|PO301000]) form, contains links to the related sales order. {br}
