==Step 1: Creating a Purchase Order== To create a purchase order, do the following:[anchor|#_639c6644-42f8-4dc8-8802-bb668aa56d78] #On the [HelpRoot_FormReference\PO_30_10_00|Purchase Orders] ([~/?ScreenId=PO301000|PO301000]) form, create a purchase order with the following settings: #*'''Type''': ''Normal'' #* '''Vendor''': ''GLORYFRUIT'' #* '''Date''': ''1/30/2020'' #* '''Promised On''': ''1/30/2020'' #* '''Description''': <tt>Purchase of fruits</tt> #On the '''Document Details''' tab, add rows with the following settings: #*'''Branch''': ''HEADOFFICE'', '''Inventory ID''': ''APPLES'', '''Warehouse''': ''WHOLESALE'', '''Order Qty.''': <tt>100</tt>, '''Unit Cost''': <tt>2.29</tt> #*'''Branch''': ''HEADOFFICE'', '''Inventory ID''': ''LEMONS'', '''Warehouse''': ''WHOLESALE'', '''Order Qty.''': <tt>50</tt>, '''Unit Cost''': <tt>2.59</tt> #*'''Branch''': ''HEADOFFICE'', '''Inventory ID''': ''ORANGES'', '''Warehouse''': ''WHOLESALE'', '''Order Qty.''': <tt>200</tt>, '''Unit Cost''': <tt>1.85</tt> #In the Summary area, clear the '''Hold''' check box so you can continue processing the purchase order. #Click '''Save''' on the form toolbar to save the purchase order, which has the ''Open'' status.
==Step 2: Processing the Purchase Receipt== Create the purchase receipt for the purchase order as follows:[anchor|#_5a48f678-622e-4c30-883c-135d7f9a0374] #On the form toolbar of the [HelpRoot_FormReference\PO_30_10_00|Purchase Orders] ([~/?ScreenId=PO301000|PO301000]) form while you are still viewing the purchase order, click '''Actions &gt; Enter PO Receipt'''. The system prepares the purchase receipt for the selected purchase order and opens it on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\PO_30_20_00|Purchase Receipts] ([~/?ScreenId=PO302000|PO302000]) form. #Click '''Save''' on the form toolbar, and review the details of the prepared purchase receipt. Make sure the '''Create Bill''' check box is cleared in the Summary area. (In the next step, you will prepare the bill manually.) #On the form toolbar, click '''Release'''. #On the '''Other Information''' tab, click the '''IN Ref. Nbr.''' link, and review the details of the generated inventory receipt, which the system opens on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\IN_30_10_00|Receipts] ([~/?ScreenId=IN301000|IN301000]) form. Make sure the inventory receipt has the ''Released'' status. #Run the [HelpRoot_ReportReference\IN_61_55_00|Inventory Valuation] ([~/?ScreenId=IN615500|IN615500]) report with the following parameters (leave the default settings for the other parameters), and review the report: #*'''Warehouse''': ''WHOLESALE'' #* '''Report Format''': ''Summary'' #:Make sure the report reflects that the purchased items have been received to the warehouse and are available.
==Step 3: Processing the AP Bill== Do the following to process the AP bill:[anchor|#_9fbacbcf-22ac-415c-ad2c-69f40d4e84f1] #Return to the purchase receipt that you have processed earlier in this activity on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\PO_30_20_00|Purchase Receipts] ([~/?ScreenId=PO302000|PO302000]) form, and on the form toolbar, click '''Actions &gt; Enter AP Bill'''. The system generates an accounts payable bill to the vendor of the goods and shows the created document on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\AP_30_10_00|Bills and Adjustments] ([~/?ScreenId=AP301000|AP301000]) form. #In the '''Description''' box, enter <tt>Purchase of apples, lemons, and oranges</tt>. #Clear the '''Hold''' check box in the Summary area, and click '''Release''' on the form toolbar to release the bill. #Return to the purchase order to ''GLORYFRUIT'' on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\PO_30_10_00|Purchase Orders] ([~/?ScreenId=PO301000|PO301000]) form, and review its details. Notice that the order now has a status of ''Closed'', as shown in the screenshot below. On the '''PO History''' tab, notice that the information about purchase receipt and accounts payable bill that were prepared for the order is displayed. According to this information, the purchased items have been received to inventory and billed in full, so the purchasing process is completed.[anchor|#_596892b3-d198-4810-9b2a-1ea07af243f1][image:UserGuide/Images/activity_OrderMgmt_Standard_Inventory_Purchase.png|popup|Purchase order processed to completion|450px]

In Acumatica ERP, you can link the lines of an existing bill (for example, one that has been imported from a third-party software product) to the lines of the corresponding purchase receipt. To link the lines of a bill to the lines of a purchase receipt, you use the [HelpRoot_FormReference\AP_30_10_00|Bills and Adjustments] ([~/?ScreenId=AP301000|AP301000]) form. ==To Link a Line of an Accounts Payable Bill to a Line of a Purchase Receipt ==[anchor|#_39df6c96-684f-4b13-880a-05ee4dce87bd] #Open the [HelpRoot_FormReference\AP_30_10_00|Bills and Adjustments] ([~/?ScreenId=AP301000|AP301000]) form. #In the Summary area, select ''Bill'' in the '''Type''' box, and select the reference number of the needed bill in the '''Reference Nbr.''' box. #On the '''Document Details''' tab, click the line to which a purchase receipt line is to be linked. #On the table toolbar, click '''Link Line'''. #: The system opens the '''Link Line''' dialog box. #In the dialog box, select the '''Purchase Receipt''' option button. The dialog box displays the purchase receipt lines with the same inventory ID used in the bill line that can be linked to the current line. #Select the unlabeled check box for the purchase receipt line to be linked to the bill. #Click '''Save''' to link the lines and close the dialog box. #On the form toolbar, click '''Save'''.
