[anchor|#section_fmc_4qx_hlb] The following activity will walk you through the process of preparing and processing a purchase order that includes a line for a service that doesn’t need to be included in a purchase receipt when it is purchased.{br}
For simplicity, this chapter focuses on purchases of only services that do not require corresponding purchase receipts. However, this activity demonstrates a purchase of both a service that does not need to be included in a purchase receipt and a stock item that does need to be included in a purchase receipt.[anchor|#_71ee16e2-b2a7-4e6d-af0b-188bed914846]((({S:Danger}The following activity is based on the ''U100'' dataset. If you are using another dataset, or if any system settings have been changed in ''U100'', these changes can affect the workflow of the activity and the results of the processing. To avoid any issues, restore the ''U100'' dataset to its initial state. )))[anchor|#section_gmc_4qx_hlb] ==Story== Suppose that you, as a purchasing manager for SweetLife Fruit & Jams, urgently need to buy some jars for packing SweetLife’s produced jam, which is sold in the retail store. SweetLife buys these jars (which are tracked as stock items in the system) from Jar Co., which offers free delivery of the jars.[anchor|#section_ynd_2yf_bmb]{br}
You order the jars, but you will not be able to use Jar Co.&rsquo;s regular delivery service because its soonest free delivery is in three days. Because you are in urgent need of the jars, you agree to pay Jar Co. an extra service fee to arrange for delivery by a third party, which you have defined in the system as a service that does not need to be included in a purchase receipt. {br}
Thus, you need to process a purchase order for Jar Co. that includes both the jars (at their normal price) and the expedited delivery service. You also need to process the corresponding purchase receipt (which includes only the jars, because purchased stock items are always included in a purchase receipt) and AP bill (which includes the jars and the expedited delivery service).[anchor|#section_hmc_4qx_hlb] ==Configuration Overview== For the purposes of this activity, the following prerequisite actions have been performed in the system: *On the [HelpRoot_FormReference\CS_10_00_00|Enable/Disable Features] ([~/?ScreenId=CS100000|CS100000]) form, the ''Inventory'' feature has been enabled. *On the [HelpRoot_FormReference\AP_30_30_00|Vendors] ([~/?ScreenId=AP303000|AP303000]) form, the ''JARCO (Jar Co.)'' vendor has been defined. *On the [HelpRoot_FormReference\IN_20_20_00|Non-Stock Items] ([~/?ScreenId=IN202000|IN202000]) form, the ''URGDELIVERY (One-time delivery service)'' non-stock item has been defined, and the '''Require Receipt''' check box has been cleared for this item on the '''General Settings''' tab. This indicates that when this item is purchased, it does not need to be included in a purchase receipt. *On the [HelpRoot_FormReference\IN_20_25_00|Stock Items] ([~/?ScreenId=IN202500|IN202500]) form, the ''JAR96 (Glass jar 96 oz., 24 pcs)'' stock item has been defined. Because stock items are by definition items whose movements are tracked in inventory, when they are purchased, they must be included in the purchase receipt corresponding to the purchase order. *:((({S:Warn}For details about the process of purchasing stock items, see [HelpRoot_OrderMgmt\OrderMgmt_Standard_Inventory_Purchase_Process_Activity|Standard Inventory Purchases: Process Activity]. ))) [anchor|#section_jmc_4qx_hlb] ==Process Overview== In this activity, you will create a purchase order on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\PO_30_10_00|Purchase Orders] ([~/?ScreenId=PO301000|PO301000]) form and add the purchased expedited delivery service and jars to it. Although the service does not need to be included in a purchase receipt, because the jars are stock items, you will process a purchase receipt for them on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\PO_30_20_00|Purchase Receipts] ([~/?ScreenId=PO302000|PO302000]) form. Then on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\AP_30_10_00|Bills and Adjustments] ([~/?ScreenId=AP301000|AP301000]) form, you will create an AP bill to pay the vendor. [anchor|#section_kmc_4qx_hlb] ==System Preparation== Do the following:[anchor|#_f811a610-8f11-49fe-9fd6-edb04d0e9b26] #Launch the Acumatica ERP website, and sign in to a company with the U100 dataset preloaded. To sign in as a sales and purchasing manager, use the ''wiley'' login and the ''123'' password.[anchor|#_ede4530e-52e9-4e60-b399-e8f65c6660a5] #In the info area, in the upper-right corner of the top pane of the Acumatica ERP screen, make sure that the business date in your system is set to today&rsquo;s date. For simplicity, in this activity, you will create and process all documents in the system during this business date.[anchor|#_a420a18b-a903-4544-9aac-6b2b7945e756] #On the company and branch selection menu, on the top pane of the Acumatica ERP screen, select the ''SweetLife Store'' branch. [anchor|#section_lmc_4qx_hlb] ==Step 1: Creating a Purchase Order== To create a purchase order that includes the jars and the expedited delivery service, do the following:[anchor|#_639c6644-42f8-4dc8-8802-bb668aa56d78] #On the [HelpRoot_FormReference\PO_30_10_00|Purchase Orders] ([~/?ScreenId=PO301000|PO301000]) form, click '''Add New Record''' on the form toolbar, and specify the following settings in the Summary area: #*'''Type''': ''Normal'' #* '''Vendor''': ''JARCO'' #* '''Description''': <tt>Purchase of jars</tt> #On the '''Document Details''' tab, for each of the rows whose settings are listed below, click '''Add Row''' on the table toolbar, and specify the listed settings in the row. #:[anchor|#table_t